            <h2>Description</h2>
            <p>
                The HTML character encoder converts all applicable characte=
rs to their corresponding HTML entities. Certain characters have special si=
gnificance in HTML and should be converted to their correct HTML entities t=
o preserve their meanings.<br>
                For example, it is not possible to use the <kbd><abbr title=
=3D"less than sign">&lt;</abbr></kbd> character as it is used in the HTML s=
yntax to create and close tags. It must be converted to its corresponding <=
kbd><abbr title=3D"less than HTML entity">&amp;lt;</abbr></kbd> HTML entity=
 to be displayed in the content of an HTML page. HTML entity names are case=
 sensitive.
            </p>
